Preconditions:
- The input array `ranks` must not be null.
- The length of the input array `ranks` must be greater than or equal to 1.
- The elements in the input array `ranks` must be positive integers.
- The input integer `cars` must be greater than or equal to 1.

Postconditions:
- The output must be a non-negative integer representing the minimum time taken to repair all the cars.
- The output must be greater than or equal to the maximum time required by any mechanic to repair the cars.